<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870924-0133 </DOCNO><HL> PPG to Buy Glass-Fibers Line</HL><DD> 09/24/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> PPGTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> PITTSBURGH  </DATELINE><TEXT>   PPG Industries Inc. said it agreed to acquire the glass-fibers unit of Tandamp;N PLC, Britain, for about $35 million.    The unit, T-Glass Fibres Ltd., makes strand glass-fiber reinforcements, primarily for U.K. and Western European construction and marine markets.    The unit, based near Manchester, England, will be renamed PPG Glass Fibres Ltd.    PPG makes flat glass, automotive and industrial coatings and chemicals, and medical electronic systems. </TEXT></DOC>